《财经》杂志官方微信。
An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
中国国内连续2日无本地新增。
China did not add local 2 consecutive days.
全球另有6个国家感染病例过万，美国新增病例已升至全球第二。
Six other countries have had more than 10,000 infections, and the United States has the second-highest number of new cases worldwide.
联合国称这是75年来前所未有的全球健康危机。
The United Nations called it the first global health crisis in 75 years.
全球约30亿人缺少肥皂和自来水等抗疫基本武器文 |《财经》数据研究员 徐进 图 |《财经》视觉中心编辑 |郝洲一、世卫称中国的防疫成绩“了不起”图1今日国内简述：截至3月19日24时，国内连续两日本地无新增病例。
Some 3 billion people lack basic weapons against epidemics, such as soap and running water. China's epidemic prevention record has been described by the World Health Organization as "remarkable." As of 2400 hours March 19, there were no new cases in two consecutive Japanese territories.
武汉新增疑似、现有疑似亦为0。
Wuhan suspected, existing suspected is also 0.
新增境外输入确诊病例39例。
A total of 39 confirmed cases were imported from abroad.
世卫组织总干事谭德塞3月19日称，自疫情暴发以来中国首次报告无本土新增病例是一项“了不起的成就”。
The first time since the outbreak that China has reported no new cases at home is a "remarkable achievement," WHO Director-General Theresa Tupper said Wednesday.
中国正在利用互联网大数据技术加快有序返岗复工，全国首批14个省市区开通“电子健康通行码”省际互认，此事百姓呼吁、企业急需。
China is using Internet technology to speed up orderly return to work, and the first 14 provinces and municipalities across the country have opened "electronic health passcodes" for mutual recognition among provinces and municipalities.
二、中国之外6国感染过万，联合国75年历史上“前所未有”的危机图2除中国之外，全球范围内已有6个国家累计感染病例超过1万例。
Six countries outside China have been infected with HIV / AIDS, and the unprecedented crisis in the 75-year history of the United Nations has resulted in more than 10,000 cases of infection in six countries worldwide, excluding China.
其中，意大利41035例，伊朗18407例，西班牙18077例，德国15320例，美国14252例，法国10995例。
Of these, 41,035 were in Italy, 18,407 in Iran, 18,077 in Spain, 15,320 in Germany, 14,252 in the United States and 10,995 in France.
另有韩国、瑞士、英国等9个国家的累计确诊在1000例以上。
The cumulative number of confirmed cases in 9 countries including Korea, Switzerland and the United Kingdom is over 1000.
世卫组织称，目前，全球超过70%的国家地区制定了应对新冠肺炎全国预备和响应计划，89%的国家地区拥有实验室检测能力。
According to WHO, more than 70 per cent of the world's countries now have a national preparedness and response plan for pneumonia, and 89 per cent of countries have laboratory testing capacity.
与此同时，世卫组织为68个国家地区送去了个人防护装备，并将150万个诊断试剂盒送到了120个国家地区。
At the same time, WHO sent personal protective equipment to 68 countries and 1.5 million diagnostic kits to 120 national areas.
澳大利亚、新西兰相继宣布封国，所有非本国居民和公民将禁止入境。
Australia and New Zealand have announced that all non-residents and citizens will be banned from entering the country.
图3随着美国大范围展开检测，美国的新增病例持续激增，已迅速追上意大利。
Fig. 3 With widespread testing in the United States, the number of new cases in the United States continues to rise and has quickly caught up with Italy.
联合国秘书长古特雷斯3月19日表示，我们正面临联合国75年历史上前所未见的全球健康危机。
United Nations Secretary-General Guterres said on March 19 that we were facing a global health crisis unprecedented in the 75-year history of the United Nations.
这是一次“对整个人类社会的冲击”。
It was a "shock to human society as a whole."
受新冠肺炎疫情冲击，全球经济“几乎肯定”会发生衰退，并“有可能达到创纪录的规模”。
The global economy is "almost certain" to experience a recession, "possibly on a record scale," hit by the new crown pneumonia epidemic.
图4我们继续用对数图。
Figure 4 Let's continue with the logarithmic graph.
有关对数图的解读可参照数说0319。
The interpretation of the logarithmic graph can be referred to as 0319.
这个需要一点耐心。
It takes a little patience.
中国一开始就在2日倍增线左侧，斜率一度接近（平行于）1日倍增线。
China started at the left of the 2-day multiplication line, with a slope that approximated (parallel to) the 1-day multiplication line.
说明疫情起势很猛。
It's a sign of a surge.
但从day3起（1月23日）中国即拉下紧急制动，做出武汉封城等一些列动作。
But from day3 (January 23), China pulled down emergency brakes, made Wuhan sealing some of the actions.
从day9可观察到明显减速（曲线向右转），此后斜率逐步弯回到3日倍增、4日倍增，day20即回到30日倍增……，说明疫情得到有效控制。
A marked deceleration was observed from day9 (curve to the right), after which the slope gradually doubled back to 3 days, doubled 4 days, and day20 doubled back to 30 days.
韩国因为早期警觉，从day5就开始向右转。
South Korea has been turning right since day5 because of its early alertness.
最终能够在10000以内收住。
It will eventually be able to hold within 10000.
日本则遏制住了早期爆发后保持了慢速增长。
Japan, for its part, has held back slow growth since the earlier outburst.
欧美国家普遍在2日倍增线和3日倍增线之间。
The two-day multiplication line and the three-day multiplication line are common in Europe and America.
意大利起步较早，一度较猛。
Italy started early and was fierce for a while.
但从day8起增速缓慢下降。
But growth from day8 fell slowly.
最近平行于5日倍增线。
Recently parallel to the 5-day multiplication line.
这意味着意大利病例总数可能在1周内实现倍增，达到8万，超越中国。
That means the total number of cases in Italy could double to 80,000 within a week, surpassing China.
而中国在意大利的这个阶段，已经平行于30日倍增线了。
China's phase in Italy is parallel to the 30-day multiplication line.
德国、西班牙大有后来居上的意思。
Germany and Spain came very close behind.
英国起步最晚，但势头并不弱。
Britain was the last to start, but it was not weak.
美国情况略有不同，主要是最近几天有向左转倾向，意味着增速加块，已经从2日以上倍增，变为2日以内倍增了。
The situation in the United States is slightly different, mainly due to a leftward trend in recent days, meaning that the growth rate has doubled from more than 2 days to less than 2 days.
三、美国建议公民取消旅行，纽约市医疗物资告急图5美国新增病例仅次于意大利，位列全球第二。
Figure 5 shows the United States has the second highest number of new cases in the world after Italy.
累计确诊过万。
Cumulatively ten thousand diagnoses have been made.
纽约州已成为美国国内新冠肺炎疫情最严重的地区。
New York State has become the worst case of pneumonia in the United States.
纽约市市长白思豪（Bill de Blasio）3月19日警告，当地医疗物资将于2-3周内耗尽。
New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio warned March 19 that local medical supplies would run out in two to three weeks.
纽约市目前急需300万个N95口罩、5,000万个外科口罩、1.5万个呼吸器，以及个人防护装备、手术袍、手套等各2,500万套。
New York City is in desperate need of 3 million N95 masks, 50 million surgical masks, 15,000 respirators, and 25 million pairs of personal protective equipment, surgical robes, gloves, etc.
美国国务院3月19日宣布将其全球出行预警提高到第四级：不要出行。
The US State Department on March 19th raised its Global Travel Alert to Level 4: No Trips.
这是国务院旅游安全预警的最高级，通报建议居住在国外的美国公民应避免所有国际旅行。
This is the highest level of the State Council's travel security alert, which advises United States citizens residing abroad to avoid all international travel.
全美已有23个州启动了国民警卫队协助应对疫情。
Twenty-three states across the country have activated National Guardsmen to help with the epidemic.
据了解，目前在全美范围内已经有超过2000名国民警卫队队员协助抗疫工作，而未来预计将有更多的州计划启动更多警卫资源。
More than 2,000 National Guard members are understood to be helping with the epidemic nationwide, and more states are expected to plan to activate more security resources in the future.
四、英国有望12周内扭转疫情图6英国首相约翰逊表示，有信心在12个星期内扭转英国的疫情，但条件是，人们必须要严格遵守避免社交接触、以减慢病毒传播速度的建议。
Britain is on track to reverse the epidemic in 12 weeks British Prime Minister Gordon Johnson says he is confident the UK can reverse the epidemic within 12 weeks, but only if people strictly abide by advice to avoid social contact and slow the spread of the virus.
他同时承认，在疫情最严重的伦敦，一些地区未能严格遵守避免社交接触的建议，并暗示，可能会采取进一步的限制措施，包括正式下令关闭酒吧和餐厅。
He also acknowledged that in London, where the epidemic was most severe, some areas had failed to strictly adhere to recommendations to avoid social contact and hinted that further restrictions might be taken, including a formal order to close bars and restaurants.
他还表示计划投入使用新型检测工具，若使用效果好，检测新冠可能会像验孕一样简单。
He also said he plans to use a new test kit, which, if used well, could be as simple as a pregnancy test.
此外，英国央行昨天也宣布，把基本利率从0.25%降至0.1%。
The Bank of England yesterday also announced a cut in the base rate from 0.25 per cent to 0.1 per cent.
报道指出，这是英国央行325年历史以来最低的利率，也是该行过去一周来第二次降息。
It said it was the Bank's lowest interest rate in 325 years and its second rate cut in the past week.
英国伦敦已准备进入实质性封锁阶段，2万名英国军人已经待命，随时准备支援医疗机构和警方，帮助维持秩序。
As London prepares for a virtual blockade, 20, 000 British troops are on standby to support medical institutions and the police to help maintain order.
法国医疗型养老院情况严重。
The situation in French nursing homes is serious.
社会医疗行业人士加埃尔·迪雷尔警告：“当一家养老院出现病毒，我们会发现75%的人被感染，死亡率高达20%到30%。
"When a virus strikes a nursing home, we find that 75 percent of people are infected, with death rates ranging from 20 percent to 30 percent," warns Gael Direll, a social and medical professional.
”奥地利总理库尔茨表示，奥地利政府将推出总额达380亿欧元（约合人民币2880亿元）的经济援助计划，用于保障企业资金周转能力、稳定就业。
Austrian Prime Minister Kurtz said the Austrian government would launch a 38 billion euro ($288 billion) economic aid package to help companies maintain liquidity and secure employment.
据统计，这项380亿欧元的援助计划相当于奥地利国内生产总值（GDP）的9.5%。
The 38 billion euro bailout is estimated to be 9.5% of Austria's gross domestic product.
图7意大利单日新增首次突破5000例。
Fig. 7 Italy's first new breakthrough of 5,000 a day.
3月20日，意大利第一个方舱医院将在疫情严重的北部伦巴第大区克雷莫纳市投入使用。
On 20 March, the first Italian cabin hospital will be operational in the northern city of Cremona, in the region of Lombardy, where the epidemic is severe.
据介绍，这座方舱医院由15个帐篷组成，位于克雷莫纳医院的停车场，投入使用后将能提供60张病床，包括8张重症护理病床。
The hospital, which consists of 15 tents and is located in the parking lot of the Cremona hospital, will be able to provide 60 beds, including eight intensive care beds.
意大利政府已着手大幅增加重症监护病床的数量，其中许多病床将需要呼吸机来维持病人的呼吸功能。
The Italian government has embarked on a major increase in the number of intensive care beds, many of which will require ventilators to maintain the patient's respiratory function.
意大利已要求Siare工程公司将呼吸机的产量从每月160台提高至500台。
Italy has asked Siare Engineering to increase the production of respirators from 160 to 500 per month.
五、伊朗迎来波斯历新年，再释放1万名囚犯图83月20日，伊朗迎来波斯历新年，当局呼吁人们在新年假期中待在家里、避免旅行，以帮助控制疫情。
Iranian authorities urged people to stay at home during New Year holidays and avoid travel to help contain the outbreak of the disease as the Persian New Year approaches.
伊朗卫生部发言人贾汗普尔（Kianoush Jahanpour）表示，现在伊朗疫情非常严峻，医疗物资也很缺乏，一些民众不予合作，导致伊朗平均每小时就有50人感染病毒，每10分钟就有一名伊朗人死于此疾病。
A spokesman for Iran's health ministry, Kianoush Jahanpour, said the severity of the current outbreak, the lack of medical supplies and the lack of cooperation from some people had led to an average of 50 people contracting the virus every hour and one Iranian dying every 10 minutes.
伊朗政府已下令关闭学校并禁止体育、文化和宗教集会。
His Government had ordered the closure of schools and banned sporting, cultural and religious gatherings.
伊朗官方电视台报道，伊朗最高领袖将进一步赦免1万名囚犯。
Iranian state television said Iran's Supreme Leader would grant a further pardon to 10, 000 prisoners.
【特别说明：以上统计，2月28日前为世卫组织官方统计数据，数据截止时间为北京时间每日17时；从2月28日开始，数据由《财经》根据公开资料统计，截止时间为北京时间每日9时】六、全球疫情数字速览：1、【820亿加元】加拿大政府出台了总额达820亿加元（约合人民币4030亿元）的经济援助计划。
Statistics above show that the official statistics of the World Health Organization (WHO) before February 28 are 17: 00 daily Beijing time. Starting from Feb. 28, the deadline is 9: 00 a.m. Beijing time according to open data.
加拿大总理特鲁多表示，加拿大政府将拨款270亿加元，直接支持受新冠肺炎疫情影响的家庭和企业，并准备采取更多行动。
Canada's Prime Minister Narendra Natwarlal Trudeau said the Canadian government would allocate 27 billion Canadian dollars to directly support families and businesses affected by the outbreak and was prepared to do more.
加拿大政府还将额外提供550亿加元以保障企业和家庭延迟税款缴纳。
The Government of Canada will also provide an additional $55 billion to protect businesses and families from delayed tax payments.
该一揽子计划总额占加拿大经济总量的3%以上。
The package accounts for more than 3 per cent of the Canadian economy.
2、【30亿人缺肥皂】联合国儿童基金会（UNICEF）估计，全球40%人口（约30亿人）连预防新冠病毒最基本的“武器”——肥皂和自来水——都没有。
The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) estimates that 40 percent of the world's population (about 3 billion people) lack even the most basic "weapons" against the new crown virus - soap and running water.
在撒哈拉以南非洲，有63%城市地区人口，即2.58亿人无法洗手；而在中亚和南亚地区则有22%，即1.53亿人。
In sub-Saharan Africa, 63 per cent of the population in urban areas, or 258 million people, do not wash their hands, compared with 22 per cent, or 153 million people, in Central and South Asia.
这些缺乏自来水的地区，不能买肥皂，也不了解洗手对预防疾病有多重要。
These areas, which lack running water, cannot buy soap and do not know how important hand washing is to the prevention of disease.
小结：中国国内连续2日无本地新增，中国正在利用互联网大数据技术加快有序返岗复工。
Summary: China has not added any new local workers for 2 consecutive days. China is using Internet big data technology to speed up the orderly return to work.
全球另有6个国家感染病例过万，美国新增病例已升至全球第二，纽约市医疗物资告急。
Six other countries have had more than 10,000 infections and the United States has the second-highest number of new cases globally, with medical supplies in New York City in short supply.
联合国称这是75年来前所未有的全球健康危机。
The United Nations called it the first global health crisis in 75 years.
全球约30亿人缺少肥皂和自来水等抗疫基本武器。
Some 3 billion people worldwide lack basic anti-epidemic weapons such as soap and running water.
